editorialSummary.text: Busy, circa-1894 Italian bakery serving cannoli & coffee beneath a stained-glass ceiling.

originalText.text: We ordered one mini cannoli vanilla flavored, one mini eclair, and one mini Napoleon. They were all great! Just what you need without going overboard. I don't really like cannolis but this one was good. I love eclair's and this one was good. I really love Napoleon's and this one was a little different from normal one. They have a sponge cake as one of or two of the layers. And it was soaked in liquor. Not bad but I would like to try to have one of their big ones if it's more like a classic ones. I'll have to check it out before I buy it. The staff were really friendly and the atmosphere is really cool and old school a lot like an old bakery I used to go to in New Jersey in the 80s.

originalText.text:
We ordered from this place since we really craved for the NY Cheesecake.
We ordered for slices of Zuppa Ingles which was fine, Black forest - nice, plain cheesecake and marble cheesecake- cheesecakes were fine. Texture was good. we missed the crust in the cheesecakes though. The marbled cheesecake hardly had any chocolate flavour in in. It tasted similar to the plain cheesecake. Some more of the chocolate marble in the cake would have been nice. Or just showed on top not much inside.
The packing wasn’t really that nice. We ordered for delivery. Each slice was placed in a parchment sheet and all placed in a box together. Looked quite messy and wasn’t as great. Individual boxes put in a bigger box would’ve been much better

originalText.text: I heard rumors about the top three cheesecake shops in New York, so I went there early in the morning. Unfortunately, the cafe opened around noon, so I took out cakes and cookies to taste. Mainly the cakes were delicious, but the eclairs and cannolis were more ordinary than expected. Among the displayed products, the diamond baci was tasty, so I bought a strawberry shortcake. The taste was decent and the ingredients were fresh, but I couldn’t say it was incredibly delicious compared to Whole Foods. When I bought the cake, they gave me some free cookies, which was generous.

originalText.text:
Veniero’s Pastry is a historical place that has been serving delicious desserts since 1894. It is known for its cheesecakes, which are creamy, rich, and smooth.

The cheesecakes come in various flavors, such as strawberry, chocolate, and more. The pastries are fresh, handmade, and beautifully decorated. The cafe has a cozy and elegant atmosphere, with chandeliers, mirrors, and paintings. The staff is friendly and helpful, and the service is fast and efficient.

Veniero’s Pastry is a great place to enjoy a sweet treat with your friends or family. It is one of the best Italian bakeries in New York City.

originalText.text: Everything looked and tasted amazing! It was pretty busy for 8:30pm on a Saturday. Service was a little slow. But the overall atmosphere made up for the delays. The Mocha Espresso cake and Marble Cheesecake were perfect! Would go back to NYC just for these desserts!
